article.headline: Pacific 78, Montana 77
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. (AP) -- Anthony Esparza scored 24 points, including a basket with 14 seconds remaining, to lift Pacific to a 78-77 victory over Montana in a BracketBuster matchup Saturday afternoon. Montana (14-13), which had taken a 77-76 lead on a 3-pointer by Jordan Hasquet with 38 seconds remaining, couldn't get a shot off in the final 14 seconds. The Tigers (10-14), of the Big West Conference, led by as much as 59-47 on two free throws by Esparza with 13:52 remaining. Montana, of the Big Sky Conference, went on a 9-1 run to pull to 60-56 on two free throws by Andrew Strait with 10:40 remaining. The game was close the rest of the way. A dunk by Kyle Sharp at the 4:21 mark gave Montana its first lead of the second half at 71-70, and a 3-pointer by Cameron Rundles put Montana up 74-70 with 3:20 remaining. Rundles, a freshman, led Montana with 20 points. The Tigers rallied to tie the score at 74 on two free throws by Michael White with 2:02 to play. A jump shot by Anthony Brown at the 1:33 mark put Pacific up 76-74. Pacific, which led most of the game, also led by as many as 12 points in the first half and took a 44-34 halftime lead on a 3-pointer by Esparza with 54 seconds left. Brown added 19 points and 10 rebounds for Pacific, followed by Solomon HorseChief with 12 points and White with 10. Andrew Strait scored 15 points and grabbed eight rebounds for Montana. Hasquet, who played just 19 minutes because of foul trouble, added 13 points and Sharp finished with 11.
